                    <span>Fantastic book for those wanting a reference title to vertex shaders and pixel shaders... Bezier curve shader deformations, color manip via pixel shaders, etc...<P>This is everything that the "Special Effects" book lacked, including special effects and correct linear algebra : ) It's almost as if someone edited this book before it went to press, which is really saying something for the folks over at Premier Press.<P>It's too bad some doofus is in a Matrix suit on the back cover and also a shame that 350 pages are devoted to an intro developer (in an advanced book)</span>
                  
              
